  "prompt": "I confessed my feelings to my crush and she became very angry. What should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your confession didn't go as you hoped. Here are some steps you might consider taking:\n\n1. **Give Her Space**: After an emotional situation, it\u2019s often best to give the other person some time to process their feelings. Respect her need for space.\n\n2. **Reflect on the Situation**: Consider why she might have reacted angrily. Was it the setting of the confession, her personal circumstances, or perhaps the nature of the feelings expressed? Understanding her perspective can be helpful.\n\n3. **Apologize if Necessary**: If you feel your approach may have crossed a line or made her uncomfortable, a sincere apology can go a long way. Make sure it\u2019s genuine and doesn\u2019t come off as trying to change her feelings.\n\n4. **Communicate**: If and when she\u2019s ready, consider having a calm conversation to understand her feelings and clarify your intentions. Make it clear that you respect her feelings, whatever they may be.\n\n5. **Accept Her Feelings**: Everyone has the right to their emotions and boundaries. If she doesn't feel the same way, it\u2019s important to accept that and not push her.\n\n6. **Focus on Yourself**: Take some time to engage in activities that make you happy and help you process your emotions. Surround yourself with supportive friends and family.\n\n7. **Move On**: If it\u2019s clear that things won\u2019t progress romantically, try to shift your focus. It might be hard, but putting energy into hobbies or new friendships can be uplifting.\n\nRemember, feelings can be complex, and it\u2019s important to handle them with care. Give it time, and be kind to yourself throughout the process.",
